unic of luclin?</span><hr size=1> Only thing I've heard so far in doing research on this is that the quest starts with an ogre all by himself somewhere in FG.  This is only rumor btw.  Going to look for myself tonight.  But any concrete information would greatly appreciated. =)<br><br>Tevren<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umalqanar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malqanar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/17/02 2:28:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3837.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fungi tunic of luclin?</span><hr size=1> Err, I believe in another thread here it was mentioned as having dropped in the 4th or 5th wave of that ring of fire/call of fire/whatever you call it test thingy in Fungus Grove. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udeadsexxygnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DeadSexxyGnome</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://wootage1.homestead.com/files/littlegnomehead.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/17/02 2:40:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3837.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fungi tunic of luclin?</span><hr size=1> quest starts with the callers in one of the caveman villages in fungus grove...give em soem beer, sold by another of the cavemen.  eventually they  go to their pull spot and call mobs 3 at a time.  occasionally named mobs spawn and they drop stuff, such as the large races fungi tunic, which is no longer nodrop <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugawin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gawin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/17/02 2:59:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3837.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fungi tunic of luclin?</span><hr size=1> I'll nip the &quot;I heards&quot; and &quot;My buddies told me&quot;'s in the bud...<br><br>Following the advice I found in this forum (Thanks all! *cheer*) I led a Fungus Callers &quot;raid&quot; last Friday.<br><br>We had 2 groups of 50-60 characters and set out to do the quest.<br><br>The details of the quest have been spelled out elsewhere on The Safehouse, but I'll save you some time by compiling them a bit.<br><br>Exiting the FG &quot;Outpost&quot;, stay right along the cavern and exit out towards the Tarmoks (sp?).  Go through the first camp and around a rock formation to the 2nd camp of them.  Towards the back, you will see 3 &quot;Callers&quot; standing in a row.  Caller Mortook (or close) is one of them.<br><br>Hail them, and they tell you a little story...follow the storyline, etc.  Nothing big.  Basically, they are thirsty for Blargrot.  Go back towards the Outpost to the 1st Tarmok camp, and you'll find a guy in the last hut (last one on way back towards Outpost) who sells things.  He's got a small bottle, a medium bottle, and a keg (I think) of Blargrot.  Bottle size supposedly changes the &quot;Calling&quot; rate.  Smaller is supposedly slower (i.e. more time between calls).<br><br>Cutting to the chase, you give one of these bottles to one of the Callers and after a pause to let you get ready, he starts walking down the big cavern to one of three short tunnels further down.<br><br>The tunnel they go to is dependant on the Caller.  I THOUGHT there was some decrease in the number/strength of mobs when we tried a different tunnel, but maybe it was because we were getting better at it.<br><br>In any case, the Caller will walk to one of the tunnels and start summoning Fungusbeast creatures.  They will come from both DOWN the small tunnel through the caller to you, and from out in the big open cavern at the center of the &quot;wheel&quot; of the 3 finger tunnels.<br><br>The Small bottle had a 3 minute refresh time between Calls, and he'd call, I think, 4 waves, before sitting for a 5 minute &quot;break time&quot;.<br><br>Our first call, we couldn't handle past the 3rd wave, and got wiped by the named that came in the third wave.  There were just too many beasts and we couldn't kill them all before the next wave.<br><br>We re-started with another cleric who joined us and a 59 Shaman and things went much smoother.  The Fungus Patch Vest dropped off the named Fungusbeast of the 2nd wave.  (Fungus Patch Vest - Shaman/BST Races/Classes PLUS Bard, no SHD, AC 21, -10 Agi/Dex +2 Int/Str Tunic, with Fungal Regrowth Effect [on constantly]...the Luclin version of Fungi Tunic.)  We had a happy Shammy.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   This is NOT No Drop.<br><br>We also got 2 Fungusbeast Spines.<br><br>Great quest, but I plan to go back and try to up things with the medium bottle and see how it goes.  <br><br>One more thing to note...the Caller DOES agro on the Fungusbeasts, and they will attack him, but that seems to be out the window if the Caller somehow agroes one of the members of the group(s).<br><br>Someone was using an AoE dagger, and once the Caller became agro, he wouldn't accept the contract to stop the calling.  He also wouldn't move from his spot, though he WILL continue to call for you. <br><br>We tried rooting the Fungusbeasts near him and backing away, but when he was agro on US, it seemed they had a common enemy and they wouldn't try to kill each other.  Only once we zoned out did we come back to find the Fungusbeasts had killed the caller.<br><br>This could create an interesting &quot;tactic&quot; wherein one might trigger the caller, have one of your party agro him, then have everyone move into the big cavern to await the swarms of Fungusbeasts.  Normally, I think they'd stop to kill the Caller on their way from down in the cave bottom, thus costing you 40 pp(cost of small bottle, approx.) per 3-6 Fungusbeasts.  This really ripens the possibility of a PBAoE fest.  Otherwise, just provide plenty of damage output to keep ahead of the respawn and one good crowd controller, and you're set.<br><br>Callers DO respawn in the normal respawn time, and the called beasts DO despawn after about 15 minutes.<br><br>Gawin Nimblefoot<br>Rogue of the 49th Circle<br>Dragons of Kel'Dar<br>Xegony <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kenshin88>Kenshin88</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/20/02 5:55:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3837.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fungi tunic of luclin?</span><hr size=1> Thanks for all the info gawin but i have one more question.. which bottle do you use for the fungus patch vest? small? med? keg? thanks in advance <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzbik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zbik</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://w