sible combinations) have NOTHING to do with the loot dropped.<br><br>That is based on board reading and the one time up there, so please test it and post here.<br><br>As someone mentioned above the bottle size DOES seem to alter either the length of time between calls OR the number he calls with each wave.  I SWEAR with a small bottle we had at least one pull with 6 fungusbeasts around.  He was waiting 3 minutes between.<br><br>Maybe I'm wrong and a small bottle = 4 creatures, medium is 5, and large is 6.<br><br>/shrug<br><br>Need to do more experimentation.<br><br>Gawin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usistily.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sistily</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/28/02 9:20:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3837.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fungi tunic of luclin?</span><hr size=1> I have done this quest about 15 times. We have done all 3 sizes beers and tried all 3 callers. Some things I've noticed. the easiest is the bottle size beer = 3 minutes spawn rate, Jug of beer = 2 minutes 30 second spawn rate and the keg of beer = 2 minute spawn rate. All 3 sizes of beer will spawn the same, ie. 3 mobs will spawn down into the cave and 2 mobs will spawn out infront of the cave. I have done this quest with as many as 15 people and as low as 5 people. <br><br>The quest doesn't seem to stop unless you choose to stop it. The caller will summon beasts for you all day if you choose. You can end the quest by handing in the item (book) he gives you in return for the beer at the start of the quest.<br><br>Named mobs can spawn in the front of the cave and in the back of the cave. Named can also drop a nice 32 AC, 15 STA, 10 WIS, 15 DR shield, good for clerics and druids. Also drops some average 1 HB, 2HB weapon, but with nice graphics. Exp seemed to be fairly good.<br><br>One word of warning, if another group(s) is doing the quest in one of the other 2 caves, don't go wandering around outside your own quest cave. You can argo the other caves outside spawns and soon have too many beasties to handle. If you are killing the mobs as he summons them, you should never have more than 5 beasties up at a time.<br><br>Sistily<br>Gnome Warlord<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=3837.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showNextMessage?topicID=3837.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3837.topic&index=18><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=3837.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=3837.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3837.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3837.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colsp